column4: <content>Ad [Addendum] Bruegel & Weiditz. Van Bastelaer 118, Lebeer 58. Fall of the Magician Hermogenes and a similar figure on foreground. The figure top left perhaps derived from Petrarch Von der Artzeney, Strasbourg 1532, p. CIX verso man bending backwards. Bruegel's original drawing, dated 1564 in Amsterdam Rijksmuseum, cat. 93, Tolnay 66, Münz 150. Engraved by Pieter van der Heyden. Berlin Bruegel exh. N° 89, Abb. 120.</content>
